dfischer.utils

Class PerformanceDataUserTransaction

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.PerformanceDataUserTransaction

  • public class PerformanceDataUserTransaction
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains all measurement data (all samples) of an user-defined transaction. Each measured sample of a transaction can have one of the following result:
    • fully passed (w/o any URL-error between start and end of transaction)
    • defective passed (a "yellow" URL-error occurred during the transaction)
    • failed (a "red" URL-error occurred during the transaction)
    • disordered (the end of the transaction occurred before the start of the transaction)
    • not executed (the transaction was not measured (not executed) because a "red" URL-error occurred before the transaction was started)
    Since:
    V5.4-F
    See Also:
    UserTransactionContext, PerformanceDataUserTransactionMap

        public int getEndThreadStep()

        Returns:
        the index of the load test program item where the transaction ends, or -1 if no such information is available.
        Note 1: This information is not available if all of the measured transactions have failed.
        Note 2: The index may represent an non-measured/non-captured (invalid) URL if a "red error" occurred during parallel URL execution within this transaction.
